						<div class="postbody">If vorbis decoding is too CPU intensive, then is there some other decoding that could achieve better performance than plain BRR and that could be decoded in real time by the 65816 or the SPC700 (preferably by the SPC700, so that less data has to be transfered and the 65816 is free for gameplay) ?
<br />
<br />Personally I think vorbis is quite perfect as I've never heard any losses even at q-1. However with MP3 you can hear occasion loss at around 160kbps. You hear them the most on music with saw-wave-ish melodies.</div>

					
